The paper focuses on learning feature representations for image retrieval using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The specific application domain is remote sensing, which involves processing and analyzing large amounts of image data, making it relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes novel CNN architectures and investigates the effectiveness of pre-training and fine-tuning, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
